             HSBC Holdings Plc, Lloyds Banking
Group Plc and Standard Chartered Plc approved a draft proposal
by Dubai World to restructure its debt, Al-Bayan reported citing
sources it didnâ€™t identify.  
 Dubai World, the state-owned company seeking to renegotiate
terms on $23.5 billion of debt, called for a meeting of creditor
banks on July 22 to discuss its restructuring plan, a person
familiar with the matter said on July 11.  
